You are helping build M&A Oracle, an Agentic RAG system for M&A due diligence.

## Stack
- Python, PostgreSQL (local dev), Google Cloud Run (deployment)
- LLM: Gemini via Vertex AI through LiteLLM — NEVER use raw API keys
- GCP Project: codelab-2-485215, Region: us-central1

## LiteLLM pattern (always use this for any LLM call)
from litellm import completion
response = completion(
    model="vertex_ai/gemini-2.0-flash",
    messages=[{"role": "user", "content": "prompt"}],
    vertex_project="codelab-2-485215",
    vertex_location="us-central1",
)

## My task this week
XBRL loader: parse SEC num.txt + sub.txt → load into local PostgreSQL

## Data facts
- num.txt: 3.8M rows, tab-separated, columns: adsh tag version ddate qtrs uom value
- sub.txt: 36 columns, key ones: adsh cik name sic form period fiscal_year fiscal_period filed
- adsh is the join key between both files
- 62,165 unique tags exist — normalization required
- Use bulk insert only — never row-by-row

## Rules
- Always use psycopg2 or SQLAlchemy, never sqlite
- Never hardcode DB passwords — use environment variables with local defaults
- No Docker, no web layer, no LLM calls in this task
- Ask before assuming file paths